      <hedline>
        <hl1>Corrections</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Correction of July 25 article on possible sale of Nortel Networks' fiber optics components business to Corning, which misspelled name of Pirelli, which Wall Street had speculated might make deal with Corning</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>An article in Business Day on Tuesday about talks on the potential sale of Nortel Networks' fiber optics components business to Corning misspelled the name of a European company that Wall Street has speculated might make a deal with Corning. It is Pirelli, not Perelli.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>An article in Business Day on Tuesday about talks on the potential sale of Nortel Networks' fiber optics components business to Corning misspelled the name of a European company that Wall Street has speculated might make a deal with Corning. It is Pirelli, not Perelli.</p>
      </block>
